  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA196-kiḷavi">itu neṭṭiṭaik kaḻintu poruḷvayiṉ pirinta kālat tāṟṟāḷākiya talaimakaḷ tiṅkaṇ mēliṭṭut taṉṉuḷḷē colliyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is what SHE, who was unable to bear it in the time that [HE] had separated for the sake of wealth after a long interval has passed, said to her own heart, putting it on the moon.</p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA196">
<l>            paḷiṅkuceṟin taṉṉa palkati riṭaiyiṭaip</l>
<l>            pāṉmukan taṉṉa pacuveṇ ṇilaviṉ</l>
<l>            mālpiṭa raṟiyā niṟaiyuṟu matiyañ</l>
<l>            cālpuṟu cemmaiyu muṭaiyai yātali</l>
<l>            ṉiṟkaran tuṟaiyu mulaka miṉmaiyi </l>
<l>            ṉeṟkaran tuṟaivō ruḷvaḻi kāṭṭāy</l>
<l>            naṟkavi ṉiḻantaveṉ ṟōḷpōṟ cāayc</l>
<l>            ciṟukupu ciṟukupu cerīi</l>
<l>            yaṟikari poyttali ṉākumō vatuvē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>        O full moon who does not know of the afflictions of the bamboo ladder<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">mālpu iṭar</term>: this is explained by T.V.G. as a topos (though without naming parallels) of people climbing up a bamboo ladder in order to reach the moon.</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent2">        with white moonlight fresh like milked milk,</l>
<l rend="indent2">        [your] inside<note place="foot">What sort of effect is sought here by repeating <term xml:lang="ta">iṭai</term>?</note> many beams like crystals bundled,</l>
<l rend="indent">        whereas in the world there is nothing that stays hidden from you,</l>
<l rend="indent3">        because you possess excellent impartiality,</l>
<l>    you don't show me the way to him who remains hidden from me.</l>
<l rend="indent">        Being emaciated like my shoulder that has lost [its] good beauty,</l>
<l rend="indent2">        rolling sideways<note place="foot">Actually this sentence is anacoluthic. The <term xml:lang="ta">atu</term> at the end refers back to the two absolutives <term xml:lang="ta">cāay</term> and <term xml:lang="ta">cerīi</term>. What we would rather expect are verbal nouns in -<term xml:lang="ta">al</term>. One edition, EN, reads <term xml:lang="ta">cēṟi</term> for <term xml:lang="ta">cerīi</term>, that is, a finite form, which might be preferable after all: "... you shall go. That, is it because..."</note>, becoming ever smaller</l>
<l>    – is that because of a knowing witness's lying?</l>
<lg type="alternate" sameAs="3b">
<l>O full moon who doesn't know of a nape of clouds,<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">māl piṭar</term>: thus the second way of splitting the sandhi: the moon that is not obscured by clouds this night.</note></l>
</lg>
        </lg>
         </div>
